Ji Zheng turned around and laughed, "Please, gentlemen, let's see what title suits this place best." Hearing this, the group had several suggestions. Some suggested the title "Dedicated Green," while others proposed "Embroidered Barrier." Some even suggested "Little Mount Zhongnan." There were more than dozens of suggestions, all trying to be creative. The guests knew that Ji Zheng was testing Bai Yu's wit, so they came up with common phrases to appease him. Bai Yu also knew this was the case.

Translate the following Chinese text to English:

(1) 非法盗掘、盗捞海底石油、天然气等资源的; (2) 以暴力、威胁方法抗拒行政执法人员依法执行职务的; (3) 聚众堵塞港口、航道或者铁路线、公路或者其他交通设施，或者非法扣押、拦截交通运输工具的; (4) 暴力袭击正在依法执行职务的人民警察的。

(1) Illegal excavation or extraction of seabed petroleum, natural gas, and other resources;
(2) Using violence or threats to resist the execution of official duties by administrative law enforcement personnel;
(3) Assembling and obstructing ports, waterways, or railways, or illegally confiscating, blocking, or intercepting transportation tools;
(4) Using force to assault a law enforcement officer of the People's Police.

Translate "This is why we need to promote international cooperation for the enforcement of environmental law and to work together to fight against all forms of pollution." to Russian?

"Для этого нам необходимо продвигать международное сотрудничество в области приведения в соответствие с правилами охраны окружающей среды и вместе бороться со всеми формами загрязнения."

Теперь я объясню это, как будто вы пятилетний: Мы должны работать вместе с другими странами, чтобы ухаживать за нашей планетой и не загрязнять ее.
